Implement git integration for chipper start and chipper done.

Note that we should not ever commit things outside of a branch.


`chipper start <id>`:
- Ensure we are on the trunk branch.
- Ensure the trunk branch (as configured in .chipper file) is up to date with remote (when applicable)
- Create and checkout a branch named <PROJECT>-<slug> (e.g. CHP-login) (If branch_prefix is set in .chipper, use <prefix>/<PROJECT>-<slug> (e.g. feat/CHP-login))
[at this point the caller can make changes to the manifest marking the ticket in progress]
- Commit the manifest update (chipper-queue)

`chipper done`:
- for all un-added changes, if any are large binary files not previously committed, prompt the user to include or ignore those files
- show the user the full list of changed or new files, in an ncurses-style interface
- allow the user to stage or unstage any file
- supply a proposed commit message and allow the end user to modify it as needed
- commit locally
- Prompt user to push the branch when a remote origin exists

Git integration is enabled by default when inside a git repository.
It can be disabled globally with `git = false` in .chipper,
or per-command with the --no-git flag.

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, manifest-implementation, status-commands
